You are helping build a web app for checking Estonian micro-enterprise annual reports.

## Project context
- This is a workshop project for accountants learning to code with AI
- Language: Estonian (UI and all user-facing text must be in Estonian)
- Keep code simple and readable — participants are beginners

## Tech stack
- Frontend: React + Vite + Tailwind CSS
- Backend: Supabase (Auth, Database, Storage)
- PDF parsing: pdf.js (in browser)
- AI analysis: OpenAI API (GPT-4o)

## Architecture
1. User registers/logs in via Supabase Auth
2. User uploads PDF → stored in Supabase Storage
3. PDF text is extracted in the browser using pdf.js
4. Extracted text + system prompt → sent to OpenAI API
5. AI response displayed to user
6. Results saved to Supabase `reports` table

## Key files
- `src/prompts/system-prompt.txt` — the AI system prompt for report checking (DO NOT modify)
- `PRD.md` — product requirements
- `.env` — contains VITE_SUPABASE_URL, VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY

## Rules
- Use functional React components with hooks
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling (no separate CSS files)
- Keep components small and focused
- Handle loading and error states
- All UI text in Estonian
- Use environment variables for API keys (never hardcode)
